{
  "texts": [
    "Prior research suggested that user experience and the intention to engage with interactive robots are often contingent on the perceived enjoyment and the perceived usefulness derived from the interaction 39.",
    "For instance, a more substantial response from GPT-3 in terms of word count may lead to an increased sense of usefulness for the participant.",
    "Meanwhile, the expression of positive emotions by GPT-3 might induce more enjoyment for the user.",
    "In the context of conversational chatbots, the language style of chatbots has been studied as a vital predictor of user experience items.",
    "Generic responses from chatbots that do not cater to the emotional needs of users can lead to a sense of detachment and negatively impact the user experience 40."
  ]
}